User Flow


- Sign up/login form
  - VALIDATIONS
    if user is signed in - redirect to user home page
    if user is NOT signed in - redirect to sign up/login
      -sign up checks to see if username and password are valid
        -if not valid - show error message
        -if valid redirect to user home


- User home
  - CRUD lists (validations - if_logged_in?)
    - C = create new
    - R = show :id
    - U = update form
    - D = destroy action

  - CRUD tasks (validations - if_logged_in?)
    - C = create new
    - R = show :id
    - U = update form
    - destroy\



    create_table "lists", force: :cascade do |t|
      t.string "title"
      t.integer "user_id"
      t.string "status"
    end

    create_table "tasks", force: :cascade do |t|
      t.string "task_status"
      t.string "content"
      t.integer "list_id"
      t.integer "user_id"
    end

    create_table "users", force: :cascade do |t|
      t.string "username"
      t.string "password_digest"
    end
